<subSubSection id="9AE1717A02889BA734A0F97A8B721DD7" lastPageId="100" lastPageNumber="101" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="description">
<paragraph id="F636B70FE9FFC970D481B90A74C87CEF" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D229F468E4033B4F2A77B497DA87B4E2" lastPageId="100" lastPageNumber="101" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
Annual up to 25 cm with often reddish stems covered with spreading hairs. Leaves up to 1.0 cm, oblong to ovate, densely covered with (semi)appressed hairs (both 
<pageBreakToken id="0BF19987D65B36651AABDD1F06828661" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" start="start">stem</pageBreakToken>
and leaves are partially glabrescent at fruiting). Inflorescences bracteose with bracts slightly longer than the flower clusters. Flowers (2-5) in clusters. Perianth fused up to the half, densely pubescent with wing-like projections at fruiting, 3.0-5.0 mm across (with wings). Wings white or reddish, entire to erose-dentate or lobate (but not pinnatisect). Fruit compressedly ovoid, 0.7-0.8 mm long. Seeds with horizontal embryo.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="379D80D0DCC9545BB755936373BD2068" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="47E8F6390A24ED2342F6E892E68EA11B" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E1C26AAEED1B833792C99A120A2C897" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Sands and stony plateaux at elevations of 2700-4700 m; common in many places of Jammu and Kashmir as indicated by the collectors.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BF0C6C96E1846A2DEB10DA5FCDC842B7" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" type="phenology">
